                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>In a note from Soviet Chargé <persName corresp="#p_TSK1">Tsarapkin</persName> to
                    Acting Secretary of State <persName corresp="#p_LRA1">Lovett</persName> dated
                    August 18, 1947, the Soviet Government took note of the forthcoming tripartite
                    level of industry conversations in London and expressed the view that decisions
                    on such matters could be taken only with the agreement of the four powers
                    occupying Germany; for the text of the note, see <hi rend="italic">Germany
                        1947–1949</hi>, page 362, Department of State <hi rend="italic"
                        >Bulletin</hi>, September 14, 1947, p. 530, or <hi rend="italic">Documents
                        on International Affairs, 1947–1948</hi>, page 623.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
